{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, discussions on GAI biases often center on English-speaking environments, neglecting the unique challenges faced by non-English and multilingual educational settings (Liang et al., 2023).",
    "The existence of any social biases in the outputs of deep learning technologies will be a reflection of the inherent biases present in massive textual data including news items, Wikipedia, books, and internet content (Weidinger et al., 2021; Dodge et al., 2021).",
    "As large-scale GAI is trained on vast amounts of data, it becomes ever more challenging to monitor or meticulously filter the data (Jo & Gebru, 2020; Hutchinson et al., 2021).",
    "Consequently, GAI models tend to inherit and even amplify prevailing opinions during the model training, leading to the production of biased content.",
    "For example, Venkit et al. (2023) observed accentuated pre-existing societal biases about people's nationalities and that the sentiment scores of generated contents are highly correlated to the economic status of countries."
  ]
}